transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Hi, thank you so much for calling Viagra. How can I help you today?

Speaker 2: Yes, my name is Glenn Smith. I've got a charge for an order that I didn't submit.

Speaker 1: I was only checking the website. I was trying to find out more about the AGV,

Speaker 2: but somehow they filled the order that I didn't want.

Speaker 1: Okay, sure. Let's get this adjusted and fixed for you, okay?

Speaker 2: Can I get your full date of birth, please, Glenn?

Speaker 1: 1-16-60.

Speaker 2: Okay, so I do see the order was placed here online.

Speaker 1: That's an easy fix. It has not been assigned a tracking number yet,

Speaker 2: so that means that the order is not being fulfilled.

Speaker 1: So let me go ahead and cancel that, okay?

Speaker 2: Once it's confirmed with the pharmacy, you'll see a refund on that order, okay?

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: Now, regarding the prescription, you were just inquiring about the AGV,

Speaker 1: or you were looking to place an order for it?

Speaker 2: I already said I was inquiring about it, see if you had it,

Speaker 1: because online it doesn't say anything. It just says Vita, but it doesn't say AGV.

Speaker 2: Yeah, so depending on when you set up your account,

Speaker 1: sometimes there's going to be limitations online.

Speaker 2: If you didn't see it there, I can kind of tell you the information

Speaker 1: if that's what you're looking for.

Speaker 2: Yes.

Speaker 1: Okay, so I'm sure you saw online the AGV is the newest formula from Pfizer.

Speaker 2: It has been proven more effective, longer lasting, and little to no side effects

Speaker 1: compared to many of its predecessors.

Speaker 2: That prescription is available in three different quantities.

Speaker 1: You can do 10 pills for $49, 25 pills for $99, and then 40 pills for $149.

Speaker 2: Wait a minute, so you do how many pills for 40?

Speaker 1: So 40 pills is $149.

Speaker 2: No, no, okay, four pills. What was the lowest one you said?

Speaker 1: You can do 10 pills for $49.

Speaker 2: Okay, now I'll try that.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: If they can do that, I'm going to want to do 10 for $114.

Speaker 1: Sure. Let me just go ahead here and make these adjustments.

Speaker 2: Mm-hmm.

Speaker 1: Because what I could honestly do for you here is then I can just refund you the difference.

Speaker 2: Okay, yeah.

Speaker 1: So you're not going to have a duplicate charge here.

Speaker 2: Okay, that'll work.

Speaker 1: I'm going to try and see how it works.

Speaker 2: You know, they say it's better, so I don't know.

Speaker 1: Sure, I completely understand.

Speaker 2: You want to try it?

Speaker 1: Yeah, just give me one minute.

Speaker 2: I'm going to reach out to the pharmacy here really fast to confirm everything.

Speaker 1: I'm on the phone right now.

Speaker 2: I'm on the phone right now.

Speaker 1: I'll call you.

Speaker 2: Oh, they got it cleaned up.

Speaker 1: The mechanic and all that did it yesterday.

Speaker 2: So she was surprised, too, when she got in there.

Speaker 1: So that's why they didn't call nobody.

Speaker 2: Okay, Glennon, your address is on file here at 4 View Road, Cape May Courthouse, New Jersey.

Speaker 1: Yes.

Speaker 2: Okay, I went ahead and put that through for you.

Speaker 1: And once the pharmacy is able to confirm that cancellation, you'll see that partial refund on your account, okay?

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: All right, anything else I can do for you today?

Speaker 2: No, that'd be all. Thank you.

Speaker 1: You're very welcome. Thank you.

Speaker 2: Thank you.
